*Swedish: [[gripa]]
{{bottom}}

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[gripe]]''
====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A hold or way of holding, particularly with the hand.
#: ''It's good to have a firm grip when shaking hands.''
#: ''The ball will move differently depending on the grip used when throwing it.''
# A handle or other place to grip.
#: ''There are several good grips on the northern face of this rock.''
# (''film production'') A person responsible for handling equipment on the set.
# {{slang}} A lot of something. (''this terminology is primarily centralized in Southern California'')
#: ''That is a grip of cheese.''
# (''archaic''} [[influenza]]. (preferred spelling is ''[[grippe]]'')
#: ''She has the grip.''

